<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3436] Groups count in distributed grouping is wrong in some case</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3436</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The count of groups in distributed grouping environment only show results from shards used in the second pass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How to reproduce :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ask for only 1 document (ROWS=1) in a 2 shards environnement with GROUPS.NGOURP=true and of course with GROUPS.FIELD=fieldA.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Results :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It will only display the total of a shard (the one used for the second pass)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected results :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sum all groups count from ALL shards.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;MacOs X Lion, Java 1.6.0_31&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
