                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13268692" author="martijn.v.groningen" created="Fri, 4 May 2012 20:43:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this issue is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3316&quot; title=&quot;Distributed Grouping fails in some scenarios.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3316&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-3316&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. A similar fix as was done in that issue would fix this issue as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13269576" author="fperron" created="Mon, 7 May 2012 12:49:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3316&quot; title=&quot;Distributed Grouping fails in some scenarios.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3316&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-3316&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; issue is for total hit count.  I need to do the same thing but for total Group Count. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13269625" author="martijn.v.groningen" created="Mon, 7 May 2012 13:46:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I related this to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3316&quot; title=&quot;Distributed Grouping fails in some scenarios.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3316&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-3316&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; b/c I think the underlying problem is the same.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13269950" author="martijn.v.groningen" created="Mon, 7 May 2012 20:00:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Initial patch that should fix the issue that group count is incorrect when the groups aren&apos;t retrieved from all shards.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13274456" author="martijn.v.groningen" created="Mon, 14 May 2012 05:26:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added a patch that solves the problem in a more efficient way. Basically the group count is computed during the first pass, instead of during the second phase.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13274594" author="martijn.v.groningen" created="Mon, 14 May 2012 13:45:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed patch to trunk. Only needs backporting to 3.6 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
